HEADWORD: Protean
<hw>Pro"te*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to Proteus; characteristic of Proteus.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧
<xex>Protean</xex> transformations.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Cudworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Exceedingly variable; readily assuming different
shapes or forms; <as>as, an am⟦oe⟧ba is a <ex>protean</ex>
animalcule</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- 3. displaying great variety or versatility. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proteanly</ent>⟦br⟧
